						<summary>

						<p>West wall of the central shrine in the Vēdapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman year: lost.</hi></p>						

						<p>This epigraph may be assigned to c. 10th century on palaeographical grounds.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of a silver pot <hi rend="italic">(kalaśam)</hi> for the sacred bath <hi rend="italic">(abhishēka)</hi> of god Śrīkuḍittiṭṭai-mahādēva of Vēmbaṟṟūr by Sembiyan-Mahādēvipirāṭṭiyār, the mother of Uttamachōḻa <hi rend="italic">(Uttamaśōḻadēvarai-tiru-vayiṟu-vāytta Sembiyaṉ-Mahādēvip-pirāṭṭiyār).</hi> This silver vessel weighs 181 kaḻañju.</p>						

						</summary>
